                     <note type="lines">20 lines</note>
                     <note type="paleography">The left margin is 2.5 cm, upper margin 1.8 cm. The text is written in black ink on the front of a light-colored papyrus of rather fime texture. The single hand is large, broad and upright (letters 3 mm. high). Diacritical marks include one stop, one breathing mark, one trema and possibly a rough breathing mark</note>
                     <note type="recto_verso">Source of description: a;  (Recto)</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>1 papyrus ; 7.6 x 12 cm</p>
                  <objectDesc>
                     <p>
                        <note type="conservation">The papyrus preserves the top and left portion of a column. Kollesis appears at 2.3 cm from the left edge of the back, but rather is no sign of it on the front; thus kollesis must have been visible originally at or just beyond the briken right edge of the front.</note>
                     </p>
